other_tests.findings: Revealed a small anterior pituitary, an absent pituitary stalk, an undescended or ectopic posterior pituitary at the tuber cinereum, and a thin corpus callosum.
other_tests.changes_over_time: At 2 months, showed a thin corpus callosum and a cavum septum pellucidum; at 20 months, showed a small anterior pituitary and an absent pituitary stalk with an ectopic posterior pituitary.

other_tests.findings: In the first patient, revealed mild central hypothyroidism and severe growth hormone deficiency (GHD). The second patient had GHD, LH/FSH deficiency, TSH deficiency, ACTH deficiency, and central hypothyroidism.
